# Change hygiene and non-invention

## Do not invent changes

- Only change what the task or verified evidence requires (bugs, validation, direct dependencies, necessary safety fixes).
- No unrelated cleanup, renames, or “drive-by” refactors.

## Preserve behavior outside scope

- Do not alter unrelated contracts, defaults, or UX unless required for correctness or the explicit task.

## No empty or noisy churn

- No whitespace-only or format-only edits unless required by the project formatter or part of a real line change.

## Coherent diffs

- Prefer one coherent diff per logical change; do not bundle unrelated work.

## No fake updates

- Do not claim or apply updates when nothing real changed.

## Redundant confirmation

- Do not ask the user to confirm facts already in the prompt, repo, or validated context.
